                        "delFlag": "0",
                        "type": "1",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a minority client. When assessing for social inequities, which social determinants would be most appropriate for the nurse to consider? Select all that apply.",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAge and gender are not social determinants. Age is biological, and gender may also be considered biological. Gender is a term also used more broadly to denote a range of identities that do not correspond to established ideas of male and female. Where minority clients live and work and their access to health care play a major role in managing health care maintenance. Without adequate living or working conditions, or with little to no access to health care, health inequities and disparities are created.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the strategic words, most appropriate. Note that you are looking for social determinants of health care inequities. Options 1 and 2 can be eliminated because they are not social determinants.",
                        "id": "382a3550e8764e8888e079aa93dc2d9d",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    }
